# browser-mcp core rules

- Before code edits, apply `.agents/skills/guidelines/SKILL.md`.
- Keep edits surgical, simple, and verified.
- Read `AGENTS.md` first; it is the source of truth for agent work.
- Follow `.agents/RULES.md` and `.agents/REPO_RULES.md` for safety and repo
  gotchas.
- Keep runtime browser code async-first and headless.
- Preserve legacy `browse_and_act` string output; use structured sibling tools
  for dict output.
- Do not log or return credentials, cookies, auth headers, passwords, API keys,
  or TOTP secrets.
- For multi-step browser workflows, check `.agents/SKILLS.md` before inventing
  a new procedure.
